 📌 What I have learned so far

📁 File & Navigation Basics

`ls` → list files in directory
`cd` → change directory
`pwd` → show current location
mkdir dir > create directory
rm file > delete file


📄 File Operations

`touch file.txt` → create empty file
`echo "text" > file.txt` → overwrite file content
`echo "text" >> file.txt` → append to file
`cat file.txt` → view file content


✍️ File Editing

`nano file.txt` → edit file manually

Used for:

editing config files
multi-line changes
precise modifications


🔐 Permissions (VERY IMPORTANT)

Permission types

`r` = read
`w` = write
`x` = execute


 Numeric permission system

 0 = ---
 4 = r--
 5 = r-x
 6 = rw-
 7 = rwx

4 > read 
2 > write
1 >execute

 Common examples


`600` → owner can read/write, others no access
`644` → owner read/write, others read only
`755` → owner full access, others can execute/read
`000` → no access for anyone



 👤 Users & Ownership

 `whoami` → show current user
 `id` → show user details
 `adduser` → create new user
 `su - user` → switch user
 `chown` → change file ownership
  chmod > change user permission
  sudo run as root
never run anything as root
developer gets limited access
only admin can restart services


